node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by The #1 Investment Page📈 on September 03, 2021 tagging @gritcapital. May be a Twitter screenshot of 1 person and text that says 'Genevieve Roch-Dector, CFA @GRDecter managed millions of dollars in investor money for nearly a decade and one of the funds ran with ~$30MM in assets average a 13% return for 7 years And let me tell you, there are some important lessons that learned.'.

Photo shared by The #1 Investment Page📈 on September 03, 2021 tagging @gritcapital. May be a Twitter screenshot of 1 person and text that says 'Genevieve Roch-Dector, CFA @GRDecter managed millions of dollars in investor money for nearly a decade and one of the funds ran with ~$30MM in assets average a 13% return for 7 years And let me tell you, there are some important lessons that learned.'.

Photo shared by The #1 Investment Page📈 on September 03, 2021 tagging @gritcapital. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'DECTER Genevieve Roch-Decter, CFA @GRDecter 1. Risk is fine in moderation. It's alright to make some risky investments here and there, but it shouldn't be a high % of your portfolio. 20% of my portfolio is dedicated to higher-risk investments.'.

Photo shared by The #1 Investment Page📈 on September 03, 2021 tagging @gritcapital. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Genevieve Roch-Decter, CFA @GRDecter 2. The best deals are private. Even though there are tons of great options to invest in with the open stock market, investing in private deals gives you access to more 10x and 100x opportunities.'.

Photo shared by The #1 Investment Page📈 on September 03, 2021 tagging @gritcapital. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Genevieve Roch-Dector, CFA @GRDecter 3.Big Big gains are nice, but consistent gains are key. Even though winning it big on some call options will give me you a nice screenshot, what really matters is your compound annual growth rate over 10, 20, or 30 years. don't like options.'.

Photo shared by The #1 Investment Page📈 on September 03, 2021 tagging @gritcapital. May be an image of text that says 'DECTER Genevieve Roch-Dector, CFA @GRDecter 4. Day trading is bad. This should be self-explanatory, but if Warren Buffet, the greatest investor of all time isn't making any trades, neither am I.'.

Photo shared by The #1 Investment Page📈 on September 03, 2021 tagging @gritcapital. May be a Twitter screenshot of 1 person and text that says 'DECTER Genevieve Roch-Dector, Roch CFA @GRDecter 5. Most people are better with ETF's. When it comes down to picking individual stocks, most people (even hedge funds) will not outperform basic EFTs like vOO and SPY over 30 years. If you can't beat them, join them.'.

Photo shared by The #1 Investment Page📈 on September 03, 2021 tagging @gritcapital. May be a Twitter screenshot of 1 person and text that says 'Genevieve Roch-Decter, CFA @GRDecter Now that I'm no longer managing other people's money, I'm your local financial meme dealer. make content that is both educating and entertaining while writing some newsletters every week. The best part? The content and one of my newsletters are free if you follow me.'.
